<br>
Do all post-50 mobs have this ability and how do you deal with it?  Is is also impossible to solo (or group without a tank) and fight these type critters? <p><b>Seek Pyremaker</b><br>
Mage 50th Season, Spec-Evocation, Xegony<br>
Proud member of "The Ring of Truth"
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uezno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ezno</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/posticons/eyes.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 443<br> <font color=#333333>(5/4/01 8:39:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=210.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dealing with summoning mobs 50+</span><hr size=1> <br>
All MoBs at lvl 50+ have the ability to summon.  But don't worry too much about how hard this makes them to solo, it'll be a looong time before you are able to solo them anyway ;)<br>
<br>
No, it doesn't make them impossible to fight without a tank.  Just don't aggro them or you'll get summoned.  Two magicians can take down a lvl 50, one magician and a cleric can, one magician and a necro can, etc etc.    All it really does is require you to pay a little more attention to not aggroing the MoB.  <br>
<br>
And, just because they *can* summon, that doesn't mean that they *will* summon.  If you are close by the MoB may very well just run over and whack you as oppose to summoning you.  In fact, our party was jumped by Lodzil once before we were fully ready and I ran it in a circle around the island with only being summoned once.   <br>
<br>
The biggest problem you will find is mobs that can gate *and* summon.  Those are really, really nasty.   Nothing breaks up a plane run like the PoG gating (or really warping as we've seen) and then summoning your raiding party one by one to it to beat on.   <p> <br>
<b>Ez</b> <br>
<i>"Good... Bad... I'm the guy with the fire elemental."</i><br><i>"Shop Smart. Shop Ez-Mart!"</i><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usampox.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sampox</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#333333>(5/4/01 11:36:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=210.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dealing with summoning mobs 50+</span><hr size=1> This is the way it was explained to me, somebody PLEASE correct me if im wrong because this is actually a very interesting topic:<br>
<br>
a MOB is &quot;not allowed&quot; to summon you UNTIL you do actual damage to it. This is why you can pull a summoning mob with malise in the normal fashion. If you pull with a damage spell the mob is allowed to summon you as soon as you run away.<br>
<br>
As far as ive seen &quot;actual damge&quot; from a pet isnt attributed to you UNTIL the pet is dead, then the pets dees transfer to your name IF taunt is on. This is why pets can and will be summoned but not the mage. This occurred once in hate when my pet got feared and ran into a rat...i saw the taunting attacker message so i ran out of our camp and clicked my earthen boots thinking they would run to me and kill me there...instead, the INSTANT i clicked my boots i was summoned to the rat (two lessons, keep taunt OFF and camp while the pet is still alive and hope he lasts 30 seconds heh <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
<br>
-sam <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unefariusgnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nefarius Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 456<br> <font color=#333333>(5/4/01 11:48:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=210.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dealing with summoning mobs 50+</span><hr size=1> It is true that a mob will not summon you until you've dealt actual damage. I pulled 51+ named in Skyfire all the time with malosi and they never summon.<br>
<br>
The pet thing I've never heard of, but it sounds interesting. My wife and I frequently pair up in Skyfire but we usually leave the summoners alone. She engulfs and fears them and then as soon as fear breaks she gets summoned and killed. Since fear deals no damage we could attempt some experiments by pulling <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> all the way</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to the BW zone and then fear them without engulfing. If what you say is true then so long as she deals no damage beyond what her pet does, then she will not get summoned. <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz, "Gnome of Action"</b><br>Devout Agnostic Magician of the 54th Trial<i><br>Member of Silmindo, Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukjeldon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kjeldon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#333333>(5/4/01 11:58:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=210.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.iconbazaar.com/people/crit_que.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dealing with summoning mobs 50+</span><hr size=1> As above, its all about controling agro. If you solo a good bit in your younger years. Agro will be nothing to worry about. Some monsters you may have to chain cast. At which it COULD get painful, but a nice earth pet should help that. (Not that Ive tested this.)<br>
<br>
If your working in a team, play the same agro game, but alternate nukes to keep from getting agro'd at all!<br>
